      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that's what they say, but isn't it kind of problematic since the original context of the founders didn't include things like modern privacy rights or civil rights? like, if we're stuck in the 1700s, doesn't that essentially mean the Constitution can't evolve to handle modern issues without it being seen as \"activism\"?",
